description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Mental Health Practitioner in Assertive Intervention and Stabilisation Team (ASSIST) - &lt;/strong&gt;a part of the new pathway for people with EUPD&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking for a new challenge in 2021? ASSIST is a newly established psychologically informed team, providing a collaborative and compassionate 12-week intervention to build stability and resilience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an early fixed term opportunity to join a new team. We are working out of Erlegh House at the University of Reading site in Whiteknights. The hours are predominantly 9-5 but flexible to client needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Job&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of a team approach you will be offering both an individual and a group experiences over 12 weeks to a small cohort of people diagnosed with EUPD and or experiencing emotional dysregulation that is persistent, pervasive and problematic. We want to hear from candidates who strive to deliver real choice, skills and a positive relational experience in a time measured way toward a successful transition onto the wider pathway offer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Some of the benefits of joining our team:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be part of shaping an innovative service development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;AfC Salary ranging from &lt;strong&gt;£32,933 - £39,681&lt;/strong&gt; per annum inclusive of High Cost Allowance Supplement (HCAS)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working opportunities and a strong emphasis on your work, life balance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Annual leave – 27 days for new starters, plus bank holidays. Increasing to 29 days after 5 years and 33 days after 10 years NHS service. Pro rata for part time staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent learning and development opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary sacrifice scheme for a new car&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous maternity, paternity and adoption leave for eligible staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced IT enablement and support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confidential telephone care service providing independent support and advice for staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;And so much more&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;“must haves” for you to be considered for this role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;A positive attitude toward and interest in working with this client group.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Resilience, self-awareness and an ability to reflect on and in practice.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Commitment to positive risk taking.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Skills in delivering / willingness to learn evidence-based interventions for the client group. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you recognise yourself in these requirements, we would recommend you apply today!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are happy to answer any questions that you may have. Please don’t hesitate to call: Simon Rogers on 07826 956 038 or email: Simon.Rogers@berkshire.nhs.uk who’ll be delighted to help.&lt;/p&gt;
